ext_descriptions.ext_description:
message_type identifies the general purpose of the message, allowing it to be differentiated from other types of message, and so be handled appropriately. The contents of this entity are defined through reference data.
 The following gives an example of reference data for message_type:


field input	- used to identify data acquired directly from the environment, for example, on a maintenance engineer's palm top;

synchronisation	- used to indicate that the attached data has been changed in the originator's data base, and should be used to update the recipients database;

action required	- used to prompt the recipient to respond to the contents of the reports;

urgent action required - as above, but with a high priority.
